metadata.name: Neuro-Daguerreotypes
metadata.description:
Landscapes with islands lost in the fog are old neuro-daguerreotypes.
Their surface changes, developing from rocks, fern forests, to cities and metropolises that gradually fall into decay, ruins, turn into slums or shelters of other creatures.
The landscape of the islands includes:
- rocks
- hills
- dwellings of elves
- ruins
- villages by the sea
- ghettos and slums
- metropolises and skyscrapers
When viewed from space, by and large, nothing changes, but in rare cases you will be able to see the whole picture.

Artwork is based on PNG layers (with masks), Disco Diffusion, python and p5.js code.

metadata.name: Game of Life: Water Variant
metadata.description:
This is a variant of John Conway's Game of Life, which adds an important restriction: water.  All life needs water to survive in this variant, either on the organism's square, or on an adjacent square. Owners of the token can enjoy viewing life survive under different sets of randomized deterministic environments with different beautiful color schemes, and different % of water in the environment under the modified rules for the game.  Frame rate is also a feature, as life proceeds and moves at different paces, and the owner will either get the advantage of something very slow to look at, or life, death, fruitfulness, famine, and colonization which seems to unfold in moments depending on whether the organism was able to get to water.  The token owner will be able to view different scenarios by changing screen size, but running the simulation again on the same screen size will produce the same unique simulation.  Some people say it looks like a microscope.  Maybe it is.  Or maybe it's the start of a grand simulation in the metaverse.  Hopefully children will see this token today and learn to appreciate the beauty of the world around us today.  This is my Genesis NFT.  Please limit purchases to one or two per living being that will be the owner of it to spread the love.

metadata.name: CHX-1
metadata.description:
Glitching pixels like it’s 1999.

Inspired by 90’s digital aesthetics, CHX-1 takes a random selection of GAN seeds, combines them in unique ways, and processes them –individually and as a group– with a series of glitching dithering algorithms. Generating fun, original, colorful artworks. Millions of possibilities. Have fun!

<<< Base seeds generated offline using personal styleGAN2-ADA models. Image processing and combinations done generatively by the CHX-1 algorithm >>>

GAN –> p5js –> Blockchain


• Artworks can take a few seconds to load when running live code.

• Press “s” (when "open live" is active) to save a PNG image.

metadata.name: Oracle
metadata.description:
The door opens; let our vision be yours.

Process: Forged in Hydra.

⚠️ Please give the unit a moment to warm up. The longer you spend with this piece, the deeper it becomes.

🌐 A note on rarity and variety: 

Although there are many variations possible within this piece, they are on the subtler side.

As this is a highly temporal piece, these variations ask you to dive into the experience of the piece in order to fully appreciate them. Please proceed bearing this in mind.

Experiment with the aspect ratio of this piece using the ‘open live’ function below the viewport - it can be enjoyed elastically. A square frame provides a more formal experience, while a widescreen view provides a deeper experience.

metadata.name: [Non]Sense
metadata.description:
[Non]Sense

Can words selected solely by their physical size (width and height) form a meaningful sentence? Can a phrase made up of words inscribed in certain frames carry sense or only nonsense?

Each poster in the collection is created in two stages. At the first stage, the algorithm forms a limited area from a sequence of graphic fields, with random height and width values. At the second stage, for each field, a word is selected that fits it in size. This happens as follows: first, out of 50,000 words, those words are selected whose width&height are close to the width&height of the field, then one random word is picked from them. There are no other conditions for selecting words in the algorithm.

Can it happen that with such a choice of words a meaningful phrase or sentence will turn out? Would such boundaries and limitations create sense?

Each work of the project is an experiment, it is 100% unique and is formed by an algorithm without the use of bitmap images. 

The endless variety of pieces in the collection is created by:
📌  generating textures using an algorithm;
📌  using a database of 50,000 words;
📌  11 color palettes;
📌  5 sets of fonts.

Press 's' key in live mode to save a high-resolution PNG file.

metadata.name: Void Drive
metadata.description:
The remnants of a rip in space time from something unknown.

- Three backgrounds
- Multiple color options including random and mono
- Four travel paths: left to right, top to bottom, bottom left to top right, and top left to bottom right
- Blips indicates new curves and while subtle can add shine and start/stop artifacts
- 50% chance to dither

Each mint randomly determines these things and using p5 noise to generate the curves from the position points. Sometimes the tear is deep, other times thin and bright. Press 's' to save as png.

NOTE: if you resize you may need to refresh to clarify the drawing.

metadata.name: Labyrinth
metadata.description:
This project is based on the C64 program:

10 PRINT CHR$(205.5+RND(1));:GOTO10

This BASIC program would cause the C64 to draw alternating lines of / and \ - in a monospace font this creates a truchet or labyrinth pattern.

There are 50 potential palettes and 5 types of array drawing methods to produce different results: Stepping, Connected, Tech, Order, and Scrawl.

Chance of HEARTS! <3 <3

Features:

Palette 
State Of Array 
Draw Speed
Mirror Level
Spacing

metadata.name: Fx(poritz)
metadata.description:
Fx(poritz) is a generative NFT collection of mysterious and magical creatures. This is a continuation of my previous work published on Hic et Nunc/Teia.

It was build with layered PNGs, using Photoshop and the Paint3D software. There are 5 features, and every iteration generates an unique poritz to call yours. There is 5% of chance to generate a RGB poritz, and 3% to mint a Trippy one.

I’d like to thank Ciphrd for the permission to use the ‘RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton’ reference in this project, Everik Titanker for the help with the 3D basis model, and PureSpider for the Github template of the code used here. Much much love <3.

metadata.name: Fluxus | Collab with Rose Jackson
metadata.description:
Generative art piece created with code in Hydra (hydra.ojack.xyz) and in collaboration with artist Rose Jackson @in_cloudlands

This generative art piece is inspired by Rose's textile work and the physical phenomena associated with fluid mechanics. Space is not a mere concept: it is an experienced reality where frames, forces and flows interact in a creative dynamic. From this base, we have related texture, movement and color in a piece of dynamic flows like our lives.

Hydra is a toolkit for live coding of network visuals created by Olivia Jack (ojack.xyz)

Collab by Rose Jackson & Daniel Oropeza
Panama City, Panama
17/03/2022

metadata.name: Hexagones - Art for Bots for Humans
metadata.description:
For (some) Humans.

"Hexagones - Art for Bots for Humans", also known as "HAFBFH", "HA4B4H", and "HA4B4HY2KLIGCVEd" (Hexagones - Art For Bots For Humans Y2K Light Industries Genesis Contract Variable Edition), is an airdrop project for owners (who I assume are all bots) of the original "Hexagones - Art for Bots" project, a snapshot of which was taken at 4:30 pm on a sunny Monday afternoon, 14th March 2022 in the UK.

This is a prequel to "Hexagones - Art for Bots for Humans for Print" project, which will appear on the new contract, following a similar but not identical design.

Instructions ::

1-0, '-' & '=' - Toggle various layers
m - Toggle the main hexagon
f - 30 second Flickr mode
h - Toggle high-res
s - Download and save image

metadata.name: life shaping itself in a whirling universe
metadata.description:
We,as a existing being in this vast universe,always confront confusing, foggy scenarios as well as starry moments in life.
We can't actually see through what life wants to tell us but just walk towards where we decide to take the next step. However, it is indeed throughout these abundant things around us and our relationship with them to let us clarify the truth, which we embody and experience. And at the end, our footprints form a distinct shape,like a wing.

metadata.name: Lush Fields
metadata.description:
* fixed version * 

Lush Fields puts you in a space far from home,fluffy,lush grass under you ... and lots of space in front of you.

Lush Fields was created as an offshoot from upcoming works, because the minimalistic focus on the grass, light and brushy haptics has a charm on its own.

Still there are lots of parameters which can change.. colours, direction of light, positions, variety
 Of the ground modulations etc.

I hope you have a good mint .. and if you are not satisfied: try another one :)

metadata.name: PORTALS
metadata.description:
Interactive 3D scenes coded with love in Babylon.js
Please explore and play with your mouse. Discover different sounds hidden in different parts of the scene.
 
-8 Random Escape Portals. Each of the Portals contains an animated material Driven by a Graphic Shader that changes over time.
- The color combinations were cut up and put into a list.
- Each of the characters moves in back and forth animations in this Interactive 3d Experience.

CONTROLS:
Click >> sound On!
Left click >> rotate >> rotate
Scroll up / down >> zoom >> zoom

metadata.name: Cycles
metadata.description:
Cycles is a study on perception of the movement induced by the juxtaposition of color cycles.
It is made of custom Javascript code and rendered using WebGL.

The size of the cells is determined at mint time.
The grid then adapts to the resolution by changing the number of cells, so you can enjoy the piece in full screen mode.

- Type "P" to pause the animation.
- Type "S" to save the current frame.

Cycles implements the "Add to home screen" feature (A2HS), so you can display your edition on your phone with a touch of the finger.
Open the ipfs file and click "Add to home screen" in your mobile browser.

@unrulyunroll 03/17/2022

metadata.name: Adventure
metadata.description:
‘Adventure’, inspired by ‘Soundscape’ of ‘The Paper Crane’, brings to fxhash the recreation of landscapes with the use of the lines.

What are the lines?

A line is a continuous brand with a longer length than width, made on a surface, by a moving point. It's one of the seven basic elements of art.

How can the lines be?

Lines can be horizontal, vertical or diagonal; straight or curves, thick or thin. But also simple or single-trace, perceived by a glance or composed of fragments of two or more lines, which to visualize them must displace our eyes in several directions.

Artwork (PNG layers). Randomization is powered by PureSpider template.
